Body: I have a simple rule setup which checks the temperature sensor value in the event data to be greater than 30 Celsius and trigger a NodeRed flow as an action. I see that there is delay in triggering the action. The delay I saw was around a minute to half an hour. Is this something to do with the QoS level of the event data messages being sent?
Hi I've forwarded this thread to the lab...let's see...
Are you using the real-time insight rules in the Watson IoT platform?  If so, you should not be seeing a delay.  Can you provide more details so we can help troubleshoot?
I have not created any Real time Insights service in Bluemix. I have configured the rules in the Watson IoT Platform.
Real time insights rules, actions, message schema configurations have been merged into the IBM Watson IoT platform
